Find the greatest common divisor of $2863$ and $1344$.
inference:
Find the prime factorization of $2863$:

$$2863 = 7\cdot 41\cdot11$$

Find the prime factorization of $1344$:

$$1344 = 2^4\cdot 3\cdot 7$$

The greatest common divisor is the product of the common prime factors raised to the power of the lowest exponent:

$$ \boxed{GCD(2863, 1344) = 7}$$

Final Answer: \boxed{$7$}. I hope it is correct.
ground_truth:
We use the Euclidean algorithm.  \begin{align*}
\text{gcd}\,(2863,1344)&=\text{gcd}\,(2863-1344 \cdot 2 ,1344) \\
&=\text{gcd}\,(175,1344)\\
&=\text{gcd}\,(175,1344-175 \cdot 7)\\
&=\text{gcd}\,(175,119)\\
&=\text{gcd}\,(175-119,119)\\
&=\text{gcd}\,(56,119)\\
&=\text{gcd}\,(56,119-56 \cdot 2)\\
&=\text{gcd}\,(56,7).
\end{align*}Since $56$ is a multiple of $7$, the greatest common divisor is $\boxed{7}$.
